profile.title: DMD
profile.bio:
Dr Tran was born in Saigon, Vietnam and her family immigrated to the United States in 1975. Her family settled in Augusta, GA. In 1980, Dr. Tran headed to California to pursue college education.

Dr. Tran earned her Bachelor of Science Degree in Cell and Molecular Biology from San Francisco State University in 1985, her Doctorate of Dental Medicine from the Medical College of Georgia in 1990. She joined the Navy Reserve while in dental school. She practiced as a general dentist for 7 years before returning to graduate school. She completed residency training in Periodontics in 2000 at the Naval Post Graduate Dental School in Bethesda, Maryland and became a Diplomate of the American Board of Periodontics in 2000. She completed an additional two year training in Orofacial Pain in 2006 at NPDS, Bethesda and received her board certification in 2007. In 2010, she was selected for acupuncture training with the Helms Medical Institute and received a certificate in Medical Acupuncture. Dr. Tran also received training in Botox injection for TMD and migraine headache from the Allergan company and the American Academy of Facial Esthetics.

After completing Officers Indoctrination training at Newport, Rhode Island in August 1990, Dr. Tran reported to Oaknoll Naval Hospital in Oakland, CA as a GPR resident. She went on to serve 12 months in Diego Garcia, a British island in the middle of the Indian Ocean. Then she returned stateside to work at the Marine Corps Recruiting Depot, Parris Island, SC. From 1994-96, she served as the Dental Department Head on the USS Comstock (LSD-45) homeported in San Diego, CA. In 1997 she started residency training in Periodontics and was subsequently assigned to 13 Dental Company, Marine Corps Air Station, Miramar in 2000. In 2004, she returned to Bethesda, MD to complete training in Orofacial Pain. In 2006, she accepted orders to 1st Dental Battalion/Naval Dental Center- Camp Pendleton where she is the department head for Periodontics and Orofacial Pain and mentor for the AEGD and GPR residents.

Dr. Tran retired from the US Navy in September 2013 after completing 23 years of active service. She has relocated to the Bay Area and is enjoying life as a civilian.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
The teenage years are a very important time in your life. You are growing up! Not only is your body changing, but your brain is maturing, and your emotions are expanding. Having all of these happen at the same time, in addition to keeping up with school, your friends, and your family, can be challenging. The Teen Clinic can help you balance all of these issues. My fellow Teen Clinic providers and I are here to support your medical, developmental, and emotional needs.

At the same time that you are moving toward being an adult, you continue to be part of your family. The changes you are going through affect the relationships you have with them. You and your family may need help in finding new ways of communicating. 
I have a special interest in the difficulties that can arise during the teen years, including emotional problems such as depression, and choices around sexual activity and substance abuse. I also have expertise in taking care of eating disorders, such as anorexia and bulimia.

As a teenager, you are making more and more of your own choices that can have a significant impact on your life and health. I think that you will find the information on this site helpful and easily accessible. Be sure to take a look at the link to Teen Health Information. Weve gathered information on many teen health issues, including patient information handouts that we've developed at Kaiser Permanente, plus some excellent Internet health care resources that focus specifically on teens. This way, you can work with me, and become an active participant in your own medical care.

So welcome, dive in, and surf around!

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Osborn is board certified in Orthoapedic Surgery with subspecialty training in Sports Medicine and Arthroscopic Surgery. He specializes in Sports Medicine, and Arthroscopic and Reconstructive Shoulder and Knee Surgery.

Dr. Osborn grew up in Seattle, Washington. He was very active in competitive swimming and track; he also became heavily involved in skiing and bicycling. He attended both Seattle University and the University of Washington. He received his Bachelor of Science Degree with dual emphasis in Physics and Psychology. During his high school and college years, Dr. Osborn worked for a Boy Scouts Aquatic program, a landscape construction business, and later for a large fishing and cannery business, based out of Kodiak Island, Alaska and Seattle Washington. He played piano seriously for some 12  years. He participated in track, cross-country running, soccer, baseball, swimming and skiing.

Dr. Osborn attended Creighton University School of Medicine. Upon graduation, he completed a Basic Surgery Residency program at the University of Chicago. He then completed his Orthopaedic Residency at Loyola University School of Medicine in the Chicago area. Dr. Osborn immediately following the above, worked as the solo medical doctor in a busy rural, regional hospital in Illinois, while waiting to start his fellowship training. He next completed a Total Joint Fellowship at Presbyterian Hospital medical center in Dallas, Texas, and then a Sports Medicine Fellowship, in Long Beach California.

Over the years, Dr. Osborn has given numerous medical lectures on issues including Anatomy, Sport Related Injuries of the Upper and Lower Extremities, Prevention and Treatment of Ski Injuries, Prevention and Treatment of Bicycling Injuries, Treatment of Fracture Injuries, and Rehabilitation.

He is a member of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons, the Arthroscopy Association of North America, the California Medical Association, and the Santa Clara Medical Association. He has been an Orthopaedic Consultant for numerous school sports teams, and athletes. He is an avid skier, bicyclist and sports fan.

Dr. Osborns primary areas of Orthopaedic emphasis include sport-related injuries of all types, knee and shoulder reconstructions, and rehabilitation of the injured athlete. The goals of the El Camino Center for Sports Medicine is to provide the finest care and service possible, and to assist the injured athlete in his recovery and successful return to sport and/or desired activities.
